Jonathan M Miller

...Who?

I'm Jonathan Miller.
I write software.
I build things.
I volunteer.
I run trails.
I tell stories.
I solve problems.

I'm Jon Miller, I write code, run trails, climb rocks, write blogs, and solve problems. I've operated as a Software Consultant for Robert Half International's subsidiary, Robert Half Technology, for the past three years, and the few years before that as a full-time software developer.

If you've hung out around downtown Pittsburgh for more than a couple hours, you've probably seen me running at Point State Park or down the Elize Furnace trail. After not running a mile in my life, I've gotten into endurace running as a hobby. It's not as torturous as it sounds, I promise.

) } } export default HomePage;
